    'bugfix',
    'Landing-page honesty pass — fix 18 inaccurate marketing claims',
    E'## What it does\n\nFixes 18 inaccurate marketing claims on the public landing page so what visitors see matches what the platform actually delivers. All copy-only edits, plus a tiny handler change to render the footer year dynamically.\n\n## Specific changes (Bryan walked through item-by-item)\n\n1. "30 days free" claim removed everywhere (hero, banner, CTAs, meta description). Stripe sets TrialDays:0 — there is no pre-paid free trial. Replaced with neutral "Try free, cancel anytime" / "Get started" framing.\n2. "50% Off Next Month" pricing banner replaced with "Limited-time launch pricing" (true, since prices are below long-term target).\n3. "Essential" plan renamed to "Single Child" (matches the actual plan name in the billing code/DB).\n4. "$9.99" / "$14.99" → "$10" / "$15" to match real plan prices.\n5. "3 family members" on Single Child plan → "10 family members" (no per-tier cap exists in code; both plans have a 10-member ceiling).\n6. "Unlimited family members" on Family plan dropped.\n7. "Provider sharing & reports" added to both plan cards (no tier gating exists in code; both plans support medical_provider role).\n8. "Priority support" on Family plan changed to "Email support" (no tier differentiation exists; both plans have identical support routing).\n9. FAQ "optional two-factor authentication" → "two-factor authentication coming soon" (no end-user 2FA today; deferred for build).\n10. FAQ "No app download required" rewrite acknowledges the native iOS app on TestFlight + responsive web app today.\n11. FAQ "30 days export after cancellation" rewritten to honest phrasing: "export anytime before cancelling, plus 14-day read-only grace period if payment lapses".\n12. Stats strip "1,000+ Patterns detected daily" replaced with descriptive "Three-Tier AI / FDA Database" framing (real number is 2,820 across all families, all time — order of magnitude under the claim).\n13. Stats strip "94% Accuracy rate" removed (no accuracy metric measured anywhere; the 94% in the illustrative dashboard mockup section was left as clearly-illustrative UI).\n14. Final CTA "Join thousands of families" → "Join early families" (beta with handful of users).\n15. Three synthetic testimonials (Jennifer M., Margaret L., Dr. Amanda Chen) removed entirely — fake testimonials run afoul of FTC Endorsement Guides.\n16. "HIPAA-Aware" trust badge replaced with "Encrypted in transit and at rest" (concrete and verifiable; no actual HIPAA compliance program exists yet).\n17. Footer copyright year now auto-renders via {{.CurrentYear}} template variable (was hardcoded 2025; never goes stale again).\n18. Footer Company column trimmed to working Contact link → /support (was: dead links to non-existent About Us / Blog pages).\n\n## Code change\n\ninternal/handler/web/handlers.go::Landing now passes a CurrentYear field (time.Now().Year()) to the landing template instead of nil, so the footer year template variable resolves correctly.\n\n## Verified before ship\n\n- Build clean (go build ./...)\n- Dev landing renders 200 OK at all 6 viewport sizes (1920, 1440, 768, 375, 393, 412) — full-page screenshots captured + inspected\n- Footer year renders 2026 (template variable working)\n- Calm Hybrid design system consistency confirmed visually: same warm cream gradient, Fraunces serif, Caveat handwritten, glass cards, ring-soft shadows on landing as on parent dashboard / login / register\n- Comprehensive functional smoke pass: dashboard, settings, support, chat, child dashboard, medications, daily logs, alerts, insights, reports, family/new — all 200, no regressions\n- Public-side: /, /login, /register all render at every viewport size\n- Cross-table login isolation re-verified post-00032: parent endpoint correctly rejects admin-only emails (401)\n\n## Deferred (captured in memory/project_carecompanion_pending_issues.md)\n\nMultiple items Bryan specifically wants to revisit later, in priority order:\n- HIGH: end-user 2FA (FAQ now promises it as "coming soon")\n- HIGH: real testimonials (synthetic ones removed; section needs to come back populated with real consenting beta-tester quotes)\n- HIGH: real HIPAA compliance ("very soon" — Bryan)\n- HIGH: build out About / Contact / Blog public pages ("asap" — Bryan)\n- Real per-tier billing differentiation (member-cap + priority-support tiering)\n- Data retention + cancellation lifecycle policy (compliance-shaped, needs legal review)\n- Dynamic landing-page stats once at scale\n\n## Commits\n\nfc66659 fix(landing): honesty pass — fix 18 inaccurate marketing claims',
    :version,
    :author
);
